'''Drew Christian Ruggles''' (born July 28, 1992) is an American [[association football|soccer]] player who currently plays for [[Florida Tropics SC]] in the [[Major Arena Soccer League]].

==Career==

===College and amateur===
Ruggles played three years of [[college soccer]] at [[Georgia Southern University]] between 2010 and 2013.<ref name="nmnathletics">{{cite web|url=http://www.nmnathletics.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=18700&ATCLID=204978513|title=Drew Ruggles Bio - Georgia Southern University Eagles Athletics|publisher=nmnathletics.com|accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref> While at college, Ruggles also appeared for [[USL PDL]] club [[Michigan Bucks]] during their 2013 season.<ref name="soccerstats">{{cite web|url=http://soccerstats.us/bios/drew-ruggles/|title=Drew Ruggles &#124; SoccerStats.us|publisher=soccerstats.us|accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref>

===Professional===
Ruggles signed his first professional contract with [[USL Pro]] club [[Wilmington Hammerheads]] on April 4, 2014.<ref name="uslsoccer">{{cite web|url=http://uslpro.uslsoccer.com/home/799497.html|title=United Soccer Leagues (USL)|publisher=uslpro.uslsoccer.com|accessdate=2014-05-02|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502032052/http://uslpro.uslsoccer.com/home/799497.html|archivedate=2014-05-02|df=}}</ref>

Ruggles was released by Wilmington at the end of the 2014, later signing with USL club [[Rochester Rhinos]] on March 26, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uslsoccer.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=32800&ATCLID=209985474 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-04-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402134852/http://www.uslsoccer.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=32800&ATCLID=209985474 |archivedate=2015-04-02 |df= }}</ref>

After winning the [[2018–19 Major Arena Soccer League season|2018–19 Major Arena Soccer League championship]] with the [[Milwaukee Wave]], Ruggles joined [[Florida Tropics SC]] on 21 May 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ackley |first1=Brian |title=Tropics Continue to Bolster Roster with Signing of MASL Championship Defender Drew Ruggles |url=https://www.fltropics.com/news/tropics-continue-to-bolster-roster-with-signing-of |website=FLTropics.com |accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>

